Whispering Trees

Among the whispering trees I roam,
With shadows dark and light,
The rustle adds a friendly tone,
In branches strong and bright.
Their stories told from heart to heart,
In antidotes of green,
With each gentle breeze a work of art,
Awakens all that's seen.

- John Burroughs
